    {
      "kind": "content",
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "overview",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Overview",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "This class's interface is common to all Cocoa stream classes, including its concrete subclasses "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/foundation/nsinputstream"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " and "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/foundation/nsoutputstream"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": false,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/foundation/nsstream"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " objects provide an easy way to read and write data to and from a variety of media in a device-independent way. You can create stream objects for data located in memory, in a file, or on a network (using sockets), and you can use stream objects without loading all of the data into memory at once. "
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "By default, "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": false,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/foundation/nsstream"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " instances that are not file-based are non-seekable, one-way streams (although custom seekable subclasses are possible). Once the data has been provided or consumed, the data cannot be retrieved from the stream. "
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "level": 3,
          "type": "heading",
          "text": "Subclassing Notes",
          "anchor": "1666442"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "NSStream"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " is an abstract class, incapable of instantiation and intended to be subclassed. It publishes a programmatic interface that all subclasses must adopt and provide implementations for. The two Apple-provided concrete subclasses of "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "NSStream"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ", "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/foundation/nsinputstream"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " and "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/foundation/nsoutputstream"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ", are suitable for most purposes. However, there might be situations when you want a peer subclass to "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "NSInputStream"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " and "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "NSOutputStream"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ". For example, you might want a class that implements a full-duplex (two-way) stream, or a class whose instances are capable of seeking through a stream."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "level": 4,
          "type": "heading",
          "text": "Methods to Override",
          "anchor": "1666464"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "All subclasses must fully implement the following methods, which are presented in functional pairs:"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "unorderedList",
          "items": [
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "reference",
                      "isActive": true,
                      "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/foundation/nsstream/1411963-open"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": " and "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "reference",
                      "isActive": true,
                      "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/foundation/nsstream/1410399-close"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "Implement "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "reference",
                      "isActive": false,
                      "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/foundation/nsstream/1411963-open"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": " to open the stream for reading or writing and make the stream available to the client directly or, if the stream object is scheduled on a run loop, to the delegate. Implement "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "reference",
                      "isActive": false,
                      "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/foundation/nsstream/1410399-close"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": " to close the stream and remove the stream object from the run loop, if necessary. A closed stream should still be able to accept new properties and report its current properties. Once a stream is closed, it cannot be reopened. "
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "reference",
                      "isActive": true,
                      "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/foundation/nsstream/1418423-delegate"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": " and "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "reference",
                      "isActive": true,
                      "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/foundation/nsstream/1418423-delegate"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "Return and set the delegate. By a default, a stream object must be its own delegate; so a "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "reference",
                      "isActive": false,
                      "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/foundation/nsstream/1418423-delegate"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": " message with an argument of "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "codeVoice",
                      "code": "nil"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": " should restore this delegate. Do not retain the delegate to prevent retain cycles."
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "To learn about delegates and delegation, read \"Delegation\" in Cocoa Fundamentals Guide."
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "reference",
                      "isActive": true,
                      "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/foundation/nsstream/1417370-scheduleinrunloop"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": " and "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "reference",
                      "isActive": true,
                      "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/foundation/nsstream/1411285-removefromrunloop"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "Implement "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "reference",
                      "isActive": false,
                      "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/foundation/nsstream/1417370-scheduleinrunloop"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": " to schedule the stream object on the specified run loop for the specified mode. Implement "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "reference",
                      "isActive": false,
                      "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/foundation/nsstream/1411285-removefromrunloop"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": " to remove the object from the run loop. See the documentation of the "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "reference",
                      "isActive": true,
                      "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/foundation/nsrunloop"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": " class for details. Once the stream object for an open stream is scheduled on a run loop, it is the responsibility of the subclass as it processes stream data to send "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "reference",
                      "isActive": true,
                      "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/foundation/nsstreamdelegate/1410079-stream"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": " messages to its delegate."
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "reference",
                      "isActive": true,
                      "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/foundation/nsstream/1410226-propertyforkey"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": " and "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "reference",
                      "isActive": true,
                      "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/foundation/nsstream/1412045-setproperty"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "Implement these methods to return and set, respectively, the property value for the specified key. You may add custom properties, but be sure to handle all properties defined by "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "codeVoice",
                      "code": "NSStream"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": " as well."
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "reference",
                      "isActive": true,
                      "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/foundation/nsstream/1413038-streamstatus"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": " and "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "reference",
                      "isActive": true,
                      "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/foundation/nsstream/1416359-streamerror"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "Implement "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "reference",
                      "isActive": false,
                      "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/foundation/nsstream/1413038-streamstatus"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": " to return the current status of the stream as a NSStreamStatus constant; you may define new NSStreamStatus constants, but be sure to handle the "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "codeVoice",
                      "code": "NSStream"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "-defined constants properly. Implement"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "reference",
                      "isActive": false,
                      "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/foundation/nsstream/1416359-streamerror"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": " to return an "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "reference",
                      "isActive": true,
                      "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/foundation/nserror"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": " object representing the current error. You might decide to return a custom "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "codeVoice",
                      "code": "NSError"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": " object that can provide complete and localized information about the error."
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
